35:29.000 --> 35:33.040
<font color="white"># That Jesus Christ is born</font>

35:33.040 --> 35:36.400
<font color="white"># Go tell it on the mountain</font>

35:36.400 --> 35:40.880
<font color="white"># Over the hills and everywhere... #</font>

35:40.880 --> 35:42.680
<font color="cyan">It's not what you think.</font>

35:42.680 --> 35:46.400
<font color="cyan">It was our minister</font>
<font color="cyan">who came up with the idea.</font>

35:46.400 --> 35:48.560
<font color="white">Sorry, what idea?</font>
<font color="cyan">Writing to prisoners.</font>

35:48.560 --> 35:52.200
<font color="cyan">To convince them to</font>
<font color="cyan">let God into their hearts.</font>

35:52.200 --> 35:54.200
<font color="white">So, you wrote to Paul Raynor?</font>

35:54.200 --> 35:57.480
<font color="cyan">I wrote to other prisoners but</font>
<font color="cyan">he was the only one who wrote back.</font>

35:59.440 --> 36:00.960
<font color="white">You know,</font>

36:00.960 --> 36:03.240
<font color="white">my uncle Paul was a postman.</font>

36:03.240 --> 36:05.000
<font color="white">For over 40 years.</font>

36:05.000 --> 36:08.080
<font color="white">He used to say letters</font>
<font color="white">are a window to the soul.</font>

36:08.080 --> 36:11.400
<font color="white">If you want to know who</font>
<font color="white">someone really is, he'd say,</font>

36:11.400 --> 36:12.760
<font color="white">ask them to write you a letter.</font>

36:14.240 --> 36:16.840
<font color="white">You wrote hundreds of</font>
<font color="white">letters to Paul Raynor.</font>

36:16.840 --> 36:19.040
<font color="white">That wasn't out of duty, Tamila.</font>

36:19.040 --> 36:21.360
<font color="white">That's more like devotion.</font>

36:22.720 --> 36:24.600
<font color="cyan">Just crept up on me.</font>

36:24.600 --> 36:26.360
<font color="white">Love often does.</font>

36:29.800 --> 36:31.440
<font color="cyan">Paul wrote so honestly.</font>

36:31.440 --> 36:35.720
<font color="cyan">His letters were full of truth</font>
<font color="cyan">and passion and he seemed to</font>

36:35.720 --> 36:37.720
<font color="cyan">understand me, the only one who did.</font>

36:38.720 --> 36:40.680
<font color="cyan">We'd made plans.</font>

36:40.680 --> 36:42.480
<font color="cyan">We were going to be together</font>
<font color="cyan">when he got out.</font>

36:42.480 --> 36:44.840
<font color="cyan">He said we'd go away together</font>
<font color="cyan">and start a new life.</font>

36:44.840 --> 36:46.320
<font color="white">It's easy enough to start a new life</font>

36:46.320 --> 36:47.880
<font color="white">with three quarters</font>
<font color="white">of a million euros.</font>

36:49.320 --> 36:50.920
<font color="yellow">Raynor didn't mention his money?</font>

36:50.920 --> 36:52.360
<font color="cyan">What money?</font>

36:52.360 --> 36:54.200
<font color="white">The money he stole from the casino?</font>

36:54.200 --> 36:55.840
<font color="cyan">I don't know anything about that.</font>

36:56.800 --> 36:59.160
<font color="cyan">And I wouldn't have cared.</font>

36:59.160 --> 37:01.280
<font color="cyan">All I cared about</font>
<font color="cyan">was being with Paul.</font>

37:02.920 --> 37:04.280
<font color="cyan">But he didn't want to be with me.</font>

37:05.600 --> 37:08.200
<font color="cyan">I went to the prison to meet him,</font>
<font color="cyan">to surprise him,</font>

37:08.200 --> 37:10.640
<font color="cyan">but the ferry over was late</font>
<font color="cyan">and I missed him.</font>

37:10.640 --> 37:13.800
<font color="cyan">I asked the guards where he might be</font>
<font color="cyan">and they laughed at me.</font>

37:13.800 --> 37:15.120
<font color="cyan">They gave me an address.</font>

37:16.720 --> 37:18.200
<font color="cyan">It was a brothel.</font>

37:21.200 --> 37:23.240
<font color="cyan">That wasn't the man who'd been</font>
<font color="cyan">writing to me, so...</font>

37:24.320 --> 37:26.200
<font color="cyan">..I went home.</font>

37:26.200 --> 37:28.520
<font color="white">But you saw him again on the ferry.</font>

37:28.520 --> 37:30.920
<font color="white">And you followed him onto the bus.</font>

37:30.920 --> 37:33.000
<font color="cyan">You think I killed him, don't you?</font>

37:33.000 --> 37:34.400
<font color="yellow">Did you?</font>

37:36.040 --> 37:38.080
<font color="cyan">I think there was a moment</font>
<font color="cyan">when I felt so...</font>

37:39.520 --> 37:44.360
<font color="cyan">..angry, so stupid that I might</font>
<font color="cyan">have, but, no, I didn't kill him.</font>

37:44.360 --> 37:48.000
<font color="cyan">How could I?</font>
<font color="cyan">Even after everything I saw...</font>

37:50.440 --> 37:52.680
<font color="cyan">..part of me thought</font>
<font color="cyan">the man that wrote to me</font>

37:52.680 --> 37:54.000
<font color="cyan">was still inside there...</font>

37:55.320 --> 37:56.880
<font color="cyan">..somewhere.</font>

38:05.160 --> 38:06.720
<font color="white">Now we've three.</font>

38:06.720 --> 38:08.920
<font color="white">Fiona Tait wanted revenge</font>
<font color="white">for her son,</font>

38:08.920 --> 38:12.520
<font color="white">Oliver Carr knew the victim had</font>
<font color="white">three quarters of a million euros,</font>

38:12.520 --> 38:15.400
<font color="white">and now Tamila Brooks,</font>
<font color="white">a woman scorned.</font>

38:15.400 --> 38:18.400
<font color="yellow">But that still doesn't tell us</font>
<font color="yellow">how the murder was carried out.</font>

38:18.400 --> 38:21.200
<font color="yellow">How did the killer stab Raynor</font>
<font color="yellow">and not be seen?</font>

38:21.200 --> 38:23.480
<font color="white">I chucked a few coins</font>
<font color="white">in the collection box,</font>

38:23.480 --> 38:24.960
<font color="white">maybe I'll get divine inspiration.</font>

38:26.520 --> 38:28.600
<font color="white">So, when are we going to meet</font>
<font color="white">this new fella of yours?</font>

38:28.600 --> 38:29.920
<font color="yellow">Soon.</font>

38:29.920 --> 38:33.520
<font color="white">Good. Only, I have speech prepared</font>
<font color="white">for when Siobhan brings a boy home.</font>

38:33.520 --> 38:35.120
<font color="yellow">Yeah, she told me about it.</font>

38:35.120 --> 38:38.600
<font color="white">Did she? You see,</font>
<font color="white">it's not the speech itself.</font>

38:38.600 --> 38:42.000
<font color="white">That's mainly threats of violence.</font>
<font color="white">No, it's how they react to it.</font>

38:42.000 --> 38:44.360
<font color="white">They either stand their ground</font>
<font color="white">or run away.</font>

38:44.360 --> 38:45.800
<font color="white">It's a test of character.</font>

38:45.800 --> 38:48.080
<font color="white">I'm very happy to try that</font>
<font color="white">on this Patrice fella for you.</font>

38:48.080 --> 38:49.560
<font color="yellow">No, thank you.</font>

38:49.560 --> 38:51.000
<font color="yellow">But it's really sweet of you</font>
<font color="yellow">to offer.</font>

38:51.000 --> 38:52.600
<font color="white">Well, suit yourself.</font>

38:53.640 --> 38:55.840
<font color="white">You should bring him to meet us,</font>
<font color="white">you know. We don't bite.</font>

38:55.840 --> 38:57.280
<font color="yellow">I know.</font>

38:57.280 --> 38:58.400
<font color="yellow">And I will.</font>

38:58.400 --> 39:00.720
<font color="white">And if you change your mind</font>
<font color="white">about the speech...</font>

39:19.840 --> 39:21.640
<font color="yellow">There's Tamila.</font>

39:21.640 --> 39:23.880
<font color="yellow">Oliver Carr.</font>

39:23.880 --> 39:25.800
<font color="white">And look, Fiona Tait.</font>

39:26.920 --> 39:28.760
<font color="white">Reaches for her knife.</font>

39:28.760 --> 39:31.800
<font color="white">Then, as she said, she did nothing.</font>

39:31.800 --> 39:33.440
<font color="yellow">So, on the ferry journey over,</font>

39:33.440 --> 39:37.960
<font color="yellow">not one of our suspects spoke to</font>
<font color="yellow">or interacted with Paul Raynor.</font>

39:37.960 --> 39:40.680
<font color="white">On that regard, at least</font>
<font color="white">they're telling us the truth,</font>

39:40.680 --> 39:43.200
<font color="white">which helps us in no way whatsoever.</font>

40:28.080 --> 40:30.200
<font color="white">CAR APPROACHES</font>

40:34.760 --> 40:37.640
<font color="white">CAR DOOR OPENS AND CLOSES</font>

40:43.120 --> 40:44.880
<font color="white">KEY JANGLES</font>

40:46.160 --> 40:47.360
<font color="cyan">Hey!</font>

40:48.480 --> 40:50.320
<font color="lime">Argh! </font><font color="cyan">Hey, slow down!</font>

40:50.320 --> 40:51.400
<font color="lime">All right!</font>

40:54.400 --> 40:57.760
<font color="lime">What was I supposed to do? I didn't</font>
<font color="lime">know he was a police officer.</font>

40:57.760 --> 40:59.760
<font color="cyan">The uniform didn't give you a clue?</font>

41:01.000 --> 41:02.400
<font color="cyan">I found this, sir.</font>

41:03.440 --> 41:04.600
<font color="white">Passport?</font>

41:05.600 --> 41:07.080
<font color="white">Driving licences.</font>

41:07.080 --> 41:08.880
<font color="white">No photographs.</font>

41:08.880 --> 41:10.120
<font color="white">Interesting.</font>

41:10.120 --> 41:11.360
<font color="cyan">They're forgeries.</font>

41:11.360 --> 41:13.440
<font color="lime">You're really starting</font>
<font color="lime">to be annoying. </font><font color="cyan">Good.</font>

41:15.080 --> 41:16.440
<font color="lime">He planted them.</font>

41:16.440 --> 41:18.240
<font color="white">Butterfly,</font>

41:18.240 --> 41:21.920
<font color="white">we have enough to charge you</font>
<font color="white">with forging government documents.</font>

41:21.920 --> 41:23.720
<font color="white">Now don't make things any worse.</font>

41:29.200 --> 41:31.520
<font color="lime">The phone here is the number</font>
<font color="lime">my clients use</font>

41:31.520 --> 41:33.400
<font color="lime">when they need my services.</font>

41:33.400 --> 41:35.920
<font color="white">Did Paul Raynor need your services?</font>

41:35.920 --> 41:39.720
<font color="white">We know he called that number</font>
<font color="white">11 times last week.</font>

41:39.720 --> 41:41.880
<font color="white">Now what was it he wanted you for?</font>

41:44.120 --> 41:47.400
<font color="lime">New passport, birth certificate,</font>
<font color="lime">driving licence.</font>

41:47.400 --> 41:50.160
<font color="lime">We arranged a fee, I did the work.</font>

41:50.160 --> 41:51.960
<font color="white">How did he find you?</font>

41:51.960 --> 41:54.400
<font color="lime">He says somebody recommended me.</font>
<font color="lime">I don't know who.</font>

41:54.400 --> 41:57.680
<font color="lime">I was supposed to meet him here</font>
<font color="lime">today to do the photographs.</font>

41:57.680 --> 42:00.680
<font color="cyan">So it's just a coincidence</font>
<font color="cyan">that he was on your bus?</font>

42:00.680 --> 42:03.160
<font color="lime">How was I supposed to know</font>
<font color="lime">it was him?</font>

42:03.160 --> 42:04.760
<font color="lime">We'd only spoken on the phone.</font>

42:04.760 --> 42:07.240
<font color="lime">I'd never seen him before,</font>
<font color="lime">and people don't generally</font>

42:07.240 --> 42:10.200
<font color="lime">introduce themselves to the</font>
<font color="lime">bus driver when they get on.</font>

42:10.200 --> 42:12.480
<font color="yellow">Does your boss know what you do</font>
<font color="yellow">in your spare time?</font>

42:12.480 --> 42:15.640
<font color="lime">It gives him an excuse</font>
<font color="lime">to pay me less than he should.</font>

42:15.640 --> 42:18.520
<font color="white">So when you realised who the victim</font>
<font color="white">was, that he'd been killed,</font>

42:18.520 --> 42:20.680
<font color="white">why did you still show up here</font>
<font color="white">today?</font>

42:20.680 --> 42:24.080
<font color="lime">He said he'd send somebody</font>
<font color="lime">to pay me if he couldn't make it.</font>

42:24.080 --> 42:25.520
<font color="lime">I wanted my money.</font>

42:26.800 --> 42:28.520
<font color="white">And did he say who this someone</font>
<font color="white">might be?</font>

42:30.040 --> 42:31.160
<font color="lime">No.</font>

42:35.840 --> 42:37.080
<font color="white">Coincidence or not,</font>

42:37.080 --> 42:39.400
<font color="white">she still couldn't kill him</font>
<font color="white">while she was driving the bus.</font>

42:39.400 --> 42:41.840
<font color="yellow">But neither could the others</font>
<font color="yellow">without being seen.</font>

42:41.840 --> 42:43.600
<font color="cyan">Sir, the lab report's back.</font>

42:43.600 --> 42:45.760
<font color="cyan">Confirms the blood on the blade</font>
<font color="cyan">matched to Raynor.</font>

42:45.760 --> 42:48.760
<font color="cyan">But the handle has been wiped clean,</font>
<font color="cyan">sir, so no print.</font>

42:48.760 --> 42:51.920
<font color="white">So, the knife we found at</font>
<font color="white">the roadside was definitely</font>

42:51.920 --> 42:53.040
<font color="white">the one used to kill him.</font>

42:53.040 --> 42:55.520
<font color="white">But we've still no idea who used it</font>

42:55.520 --> 42:58.200
<font color="white">or how they did it</font>
<font color="white">without anyone else noticing.</font>

42:59.640 --> 43:01.080
<font color="lime">Someone looking for me?</font>

43:03.280 --> 43:04.920
<font color="lime">I'm Errol Porter.</font>

43:08.160 --> 43:09.760
<font color="white">You're Errol Porter?</font>

43:09.760 --> 43:10.880
<font color="lime">Mm.</font>

43:17.000 --> 43:18.880
<font color="white">These are yours?</font>

43:18.880 --> 43:20.120
<font color="lime">Yes, sir.</font>

43:20.120 --> 43:21.120
<font color="white">Seriously?</font>

43:21.120 --> 43:22.560
<font color="lime">They've got my name in. Look.</font>

43:22.560 --> 43:23.960
<font color="white">You lost them?</font>

43:23.960 --> 43:26.640
<font color="lime">No. No. I know exactly</font>
<font color="lime">where they were.</font>

43:26.640 --> 43:28.240
<font color="lime">I just lost the locker key.</font>

43:28.240 --> 43:30.120
<font color="white">You lost the key?</font>

43:30.120 --> 43:31.560
<font color="lime">Yeah.</font>

43:31.560 --> 43:34.640
<font color="white">Have you ever heard of</font>
<font color="white">a man called Paul Raynor?</font>

43:34.640 --> 43:36.400
<font color="lime">No.</font>

43:36.400 --> 43:38.600
<font color="lime">So, can I take them?</font>

43:38.600 --> 43:40.440
<font color="white">HE SIGHS</font>

43:50.680 --> 43:53.680
<font color="white">Mr Porter, do you remember</font>
<font color="white">where you lost the key?</font>

43:56.080 --> 43:57.920
<font color="white">JP, where's the key? Quick.</font>

44:32.640 --> 44:35.400
<font color="white">Please, sit in the seats that you</font>
<font color="white">were sitting in in the journey.</font>

44:35.400 --> 44:37.120
<font color="cyan">We found it, sir.</font>

44:37.120 --> 44:38.960
<font color="cyan">Right by the roadside.</font>

44:43.840 --> 44:46.240
<font color="white">JP, financial records,</font>
<font color="white">full background check, please.</font>

44:47.480 --> 44:48.880
<font color="yellow">I don't understand.</font>

44:48.880 --> 44:51.160
<font color="white">Oh, Florence, I need the original</font>
<font color="white">police file</font>

44:51.160 --> 44:52.720
<font color="white">from the Ocean Casino robbery.</font>

45:00.040 --> 45:01.480
<font color="yellow">He worked at the Ocean Casino?</font>

45:01.480 --> 45:03.320
<font color="cyan">Yeah. Kitchens.</font>

45:03.320 --> 45:05.960
<font color="lime">What you probably don't know is</font>
<font color="lime">the money stolen that night</font>

45:05.960 --> 45:07.200
<font color="lime">has never been recovered.</font>

45:07.200 --> 45:08.960
<font color="white">How did the money get to</font>
<font color="white">Saint Marie?</font>

45:10.760 --> 45:12.240
<font color="yellow">Sir.</font>

45:18.560 --> 45:19.760
<font color="white">Gotcha.</font>

45:19.760 --> 45:22.040
<font color="white">JP! </font><font color="cyan">Yeah? Just coming up, sir.</font>

45:24.040 --> 45:25.240
<font color="white">Back to the beginning.</font>

45:25.240 --> 45:27.920
<font color="white">Back, back, back. Stop right there.</font>

45:27.920 --> 45:30.480
<font color="white">Florence, get everyone together</font>
<font color="white">at the bus depot.</font>

45:30.480 --> 45:34.400
<font color="white">JP,</font>
<font color="white">one last job when we get there.</font>

45:38.400 --> 45:39.680
<font color="white">Great stuff.</font>

45:39.680 --> 45:42.720
<font color="white">You're all here, and all in the</font>
<font color="white">same seats you were sitting in</font>

45:42.720 --> 45:46.040
<font color="white">on the day that Paul Raynor</font>
<font color="white">was murdered in cold blood.</font>

45:46.040 --> 45:49.640
<font color="white">Apart from Harold, who very kindly</font>
<font color="white">agreed to stand in for Raynor again</font>

45:49.640 --> 45:51.840
<font color="white">for the purposes of this</font>
<font color="white">little demonstration.</font>

45:51.840 --> 45:53.680
<font color="white">I do love a bus.</font>

45:55.120 --> 45:57.640
<font color="white">It's one of the few things</font>
<font color="white">guaranteed to transport me</font>

45:57.640 --> 45:59.520
<font color="white">back to my own childhood.</font>

45:59.520 --> 46:00.840
<font color="white">All at the sound of a bell.</font>

46:00.840 --> 46:02.600
<font color="white">BELL RINGS</font>

46:02.600 --> 46:04.880
<font color="white">One little press of the bell</font>
<font color="white">and I'm 14 again.</font>

46:04.880 --> 46:07.960
<font color="white">Sitting on the back seat</font>
<font color="white">with Kathleen O'Brien.</font>

46:09.720 --> 46:11.680
<font color="white">Sneaking a little kiss,</font>

46:11.680 --> 46:13.400
<font color="white">giving her about my jam sandwich.</font>

46:13.400 --> 46:15.240
<font color="yellow">Sir.</font>

46:15.240 --> 46:17.400
<font color="white">Yes, Florence. Thank you.</font>

46:18.600 --> 46:19.800
<font color="white">Right.</font>

46:19.800 --> 46:21.520
<font color="white">A man is killed on a bus.</font>

46:21.520 --> 46:25.880
<font color="white">There are four other people on</font>
<font color="white">the bus, including the driver.</font>

46:25.880 --> 46:28.600
<font color="white">Yet none of them saw the murder</font>
<font color="white">happen. How is this possible?</font>

46:28.600 --> 46:32.360
<font color="white">Well, of course the simple truth</font>
<font color="white">is that it isn't.</font>

46:34.720 --> 46:37.360
<font color="white">You see, things were a bit</font>
<font color="white">complicated by the fact that,</font>

46:37.360 --> 46:41.240
<font color="white">quite by chance as it turns out,</font>
<font color="white">everyone on the bus that day</font>

46:41.240 --> 46:43.560
<font color="white">with Paul Raynor had a reason</font>
<font color="white">to want him dead.</font>

46:44.880 --> 46:48.560
<font color="white">And that was the problem. We</font>
<font color="white">couldn't see the wood for the trees.</font>

46:48.560 --> 46:50.240
<font color="white">You know, where normally,</font>

46:50.240 --> 46:52.800
<font color="white">we struggle to find means</font>
<font color="white">and motive and opportunity,</font>

46:52.800 --> 46:54.640
<font color="white">we had nothing but.</font>

46:54.640 --> 46:57.280
<font color="white">And so finally we have to come</font>
<font color="white">back to the same thing,</font>

46:57.280 --> 46:58.880
<font color="white">the same simple truth...</font>

47:00.000 --> 47:03.040
<font color="white">..if it was impossible for any of</font>
<font color="white">you to have killed Raynor without</font>

47:03.040 --> 47:04.400
<font color="white">being seen by the others,</font>

47:04.400 --> 47:06.840
<font color="white">then that isn't what happened.</font>

47:06.840 --> 47:09.280
<font color="yellow">I don't understand. Are you saying</font>
<font color="yellow">none of us killed him?</font>

47:09.280 --> 47:12.280
<font color="white">Yes, I'm saying no-one on the bus</font>
<font color="white">that day murdered Paul Raynor.</font>

47:13.560 --> 47:14.920
<font color="yellow">But then who did?</font>

47:14.920 --> 47:16.160
<font color="cyan">And how?</font>

47:16.160 --> 47:18.600
<font color="cyan">If no-one could get on the bus.</font>

47:18.600 --> 47:23.080
<font color="white">Two excellent questions. And</font>
<font color="white">the second one answers the first.</font>

47:23.080 --> 47:27.560
<font color="white">You see, someone else got</font>
<font color="white">on the bus using the emergency door.</font>

47:27.560 --> 47:29.160
<font color="lime">But it doesn't open.</font>

47:29.160 --> 47:32.600
<font color="white">Not from the outside, no, but</font>
<font color="white">it can be opened from the inside.</font>

47:32.600 --> 47:34.600
<font color="white">But none of you opened it.</font>

47:34.600 --> 47:36.520
<font color="white">Why would you?</font>

47:36.520 --> 47:40.200
<font color="white">In fact, the only person who could</font>
<font color="white">have opened it was Raynor himself.</font>

47:40.200 --> 47:42.160
<font color="yellow">But why did he do that?</font>

47:42.160 --> 47:45.200
<font color="white">Well, he didn't know he was</font>
<font color="white">opening it to his killer.</font>

47:45.200 --> 47:47.040
<font color="white">You see, he thought it was a friend.</font>

47:54.360 --> 47:56.200
<font color="white">Didn't he, Harold?</font>

47:57.960 --> 48:01.200
<font color="white">You were the only one who was</font>
<font color="white">never really under suspicion.</font>

48:01.200 --> 48:03.880
<font color="white">And why would you be?</font>
<font color="white">You weren't even on the bus.</font>

48:03.880 --> 48:06.960
<font color="white">And, to my shame, we didn't even</font>
<font color="white">look into your background.</font>

48:06.960 --> 48:09.760
<font color="white">If we did, we would have discovered</font>
<font color="white">that you were working at the</font>

48:09.760 --> 48:13.400
<font color="white">Ocean Casino in Guadeloupe</font>
<font color="white">around the time of the robbery.</font>

48:13.400 --> 48:15.080
<font color="white">According to the casino records,</font>

48:15.080 --> 48:17.160
<font color="white">you started a month</font>
<font color="white">before the robbery,</font>

48:17.160 --> 48:19.160
<font color="white">and you left about a week after it.</font>

48:19.160 --> 48:23.400
<font color="yellow">The police files clearly said that</font>
<font color="yellow">rear exit doors to the casino</font>

48:23.400 --> 48:25.160
<font color="yellow">were opened from the inside.</font>

48:25.160 --> 48:28.880
<font color="yellow">A month after leaving the casino,</font>
<font color="yellow">you moved to Saint Marie.</font>

48:28.880 --> 48:30.800
<font color="white">And a couple of months after that,</font>

48:30.800 --> 48:32.720
<font color="white">you started your</font>
<font color="white">own transport business.</font>

48:32.720 --> 48:35.000
<font color="white">And you bought a lovely villa</font>
<font color="white">up in the hills, didn't you?</font>

48:35.000 --> 48:39.520
<font color="lime">We set up in 2004,</font>
<font color="lime">and she joined a year later.</font>

48:39.520 --> 48:42.680
<font color="white">Using the three quarters of a</font>
<font color="white">million euros that you were supposed</font>

48:42.680 --> 48:45.760
<font color="white">to be looking after once your</font>
<font color="white">partner in crime had been arrested.</font>

48:45.760 --> 48:49.840
<font color="white">Paul Raynor came to Saint Marie</font>
<font color="white">to collect his half of the money.</font>

48:49.840 --> 48:51.840
<font color="white">But it was already gone, wasn't it?</font>

48:56.680 --> 49:00.560
<font color="white">It was the locker key found on</font>
<font color="white">Raynor's body that pointed the way.</font>

49:00.560 --> 49:04.400
<font color="white">But when we went to open that</font>
<font color="white">locker, there was nothing there.</font>

49:05.680 --> 49:07.680
<font color="white">Apart from a pair</font>
<font color="white">of old swimming trunks.</font>

49:08.920 --> 49:11.720
<font color="white">So we traced the owner and he</font>
<font color="white">told us he'd lost his locker key</font>

49:11.720 --> 49:12.960
<font color="white">two weeks ago.</font>

49:12.960 --> 49:15.200
<font color="white">Do you remember</font>
<font color="white">where you lost the key?</font>

49:15.200 --> 49:17.880
<font color="lime">On the beach or the bus.</font>

49:20.480 --> 49:23.320
<font color="cyan">The lost property logs show there</font>
<font color="cyan">was a key found two weeks ago.</font>

49:23.320 --> 49:28.040
<font color="cyan">There is no record of it being</font>
<font color="cyan">cleaned. So I searched the box.</font>

49:28.040 --> 49:29.440
<font color="cyan">It's not there.</font>

49:29.440 --> 49:30.840
<font color="white">Of course it isn't.</font>

49:30.840 --> 49:33.480
<font color="white">Because Raynor came here</font>
<font color="white">for his money,</font>

49:33.480 --> 49:35.080
<font color="white">the money that you'd already spent,</font>

49:35.080 --> 49:36.560
<font color="white">which is why you had to stop him.</font>

49:38.560 --> 49:41.120
<font color="white">So you came up with a plan, one that</font>
<font color="white">would make Raynor think</font>

49:41.120 --> 49:43.440
<font color="white">that you were going to give him</font>
<font color="white">his share of the cash.</font>

49:43.440 --> 49:46.680
<font color="white">Now, for the plan to work,</font>
<font color="white">you couldn't meet him in person.</font>

49:48.120 --> 49:50.200
<font color="white">So you needed an excuse</font>
<font color="white">that he'd buy.</font>

49:50.200 --> 49:53.960
<font color="white">Maybe you told him it was to risky</font>
<font color="white">to meet face-to-face.</font>

49:53.960 --> 49:57.440
<font color="white">Instead, you told him</font>
<font color="white">you'd plant a key for him to find.</font>

49:59.040 --> 50:01.480
<font color="white">Of course, Butterfly didn't know</font>
<font color="white">it was Raynor on her bus.</font>

50:01.480 --> 50:03.520
<font color="white">How could she?</font>

50:03.520 --> 50:05.160
<font color="white">But you did.</font>

50:05.160 --> 50:08.240
<font color="white">Because you told him his money</font>
<font color="white">was safe in the locker and that</font>

50:08.240 --> 50:10.640
<font color="white">the key would be taped</font>
<font color="white">under the back seat of the bus.</font>

50:10.640 --> 50:13.320
<font color="white">And I dare say you also knew</font>
<font color="white">someone in that prison who was able</font>

50:13.320 --> 50:15.040
<font color="white">to recommend a good forger.</font>

50:15.040 --> 50:17.560
<font color="yellow">Does your boss know what you do</font>
<font color="yellow">in your spare time?</font>

50:17.560 --> 50:20.400
<font color="lime">It gives him an excuse to pay me</font>
<font color="lime">less than he should.</font>

50:20.400 --> 50:24.080
<font color="white">So you used the phone in</font>
<font color="white">the barber shop, and that way,</font>

50:24.080 --> 50:26.920
<font color="white">you could contact Raynor without</font>
<font color="white">anyone being able to trace</font>

50:26.920 --> 50:28.320
<font color="white">the calls back to you.</font>

50:29.600 --> 50:32.880
<font color="white">You know, when I asked you to</font>
<font color="white">stand in for Raynor the first time,</font>

50:32.880 --> 50:35.840
<font color="white">we should have known, should have</font>
<font color="white">known that you sitting in</font>

50:35.840 --> 50:38.080
<font color="white">exactly the right seat</font>
<font color="white">wasn't a coincidence.</font>

50:38.080 --> 50:40.280
<font color="white">It's because you knew</font>
<font color="white">where you left the key.</font>

50:40.280 --> 50:43.840
<font color="white">It didn't matter that there was</font>
<font color="white">no money in the locker -</font>

50:43.840 --> 50:47.240
<font color="white">Raynor wasn't going to live</font>
<font color="white">long enough to find that out.</font>

50:47.240 --> 50:50.280
<font color="white">All that mattered was that</font>
<font color="white">he believed it was there.</font>

50:51.520 --> 50:53.080
<font color="white">This key</font>

50:53.080 --> 50:54.240
<font color="white">isn't really a key at all.</font>

50:55.520 --> 50:57.560
<font color="white">It was bait, for a trap.</font>

50:58.840 --> 51:01.840
<font color="white">A way to make sure that Raynor was</font>
<font color="white">sitting beside the emergency door.</font>

51:03.880 --> 51:07.120
<font color="white">Raynor found the key exactly</font>
<font color="white">where you said it would be.</font>

51:14.200 --> 51:17.600
<font color="white">When the bus arrived at the station,</font>
<font color="white">you were there waiting for him.</font>

51:19.320 --> 51:21.080
<font color="white">You knew exactly where Raynor</font>
<font color="white">was sitting.</font>

51:21.080 --> 51:23.160
<font color="white">You knew about the faulty door.</font>

51:23.160 --> 51:26.320
<font color="white">You also knew that all it would</font>
<font color="white">take for Raynor to open that door</font>

51:26.320 --> 51:28.000
<font color="white">would be a simple knock</font>
<font color="white">on the window.</font>

51:31.240 --> 51:33.120
<font color="white">Of course Raynor opened the door,</font>

51:33.120 --> 51:36.120
<font color="white">while everyone else was distracted.</font>

51:36.120 --> 51:38.320
<font color="white">I bet he didn't know what hit him.</font>

51:42.280 --> 51:44.520
<font color="white">Deed done, you closed the door.</font>

51:57.880 --> 52:00.120
<font color="white">But Harold wasn't finished yet.</font>

52:00.120 --> 52:03.400
<font color="white">Oh, he had one more trick</font>
<font color="white">to throw us off the scent.</font>

52:04.440 --> 52:06.240
<font color="white">The knife on the road.</font>

52:06.240 --> 52:09.160
<font color="yellow">When Officer Hooper</font>
<font color="yellow">found it outside on the lane,</font>

52:09.160 --> 52:13.320
<font color="yellow">we assumed it had been thrown from</font>
<font color="yellow">the bus window during the journey.</font>

52:13.320 --> 52:16.960
<font color="white">Making us think that Raynor</font>
<font color="white">was killed by one</font>
<font color="white">of the other passengers.</font>

52:16.960 --> 52:21.440
<font color="yellow">When in fact you planted the knife</font>
<font color="yellow">on the road for us to find</font>

52:21.440 --> 52:24.520
<font color="yellow">a few hours after you killed Raynor.</font>

52:26.480 --> 52:28.760
<font color="white">You did what you did</font>
<font color="white">to protect what you had.</font>

52:29.880 --> 52:31.400
<font color="white">And in doing so, you lost it.</font>

52:34.640 --> 52:36.320
<font color="white">I think you'll find</font>
<font color="white">this is your stop.</font>

52:37.920 --> 52:39.720
<font color="white">BELL RINGS</font>

52:40.760 --> 52:42.040
<font color="white">JP.</font>

52:48.280 --> 52:50.120
<font color="cyan">Up.</font>

52:58.680 --> 53:00.520
<font color="lime">I've heard a lot of strange things,</font>

53:00.520 --> 53:05.040
<font color="lime">but solving a murder using a pair</font>
<font color="lime">of mouldy swimming trunks</font>

53:05.040 --> 53:06.960
<font color="lime">tops everything.</font>

53:06.960 --> 53:08.880
<font color="white">God bless Errol's budgie smugglers.</font>

53:08.880 --> 53:11.760
<font color="cyan">To Errol. </font><font color="lime">What is a budgie smuggler?</font>

53:11.760 --> 53:13.440
<font color="white">It's a long story, Catherine.</font>

53:15.480 --> 53:17.520
<font color="white">Oh. Florence.</font>

53:18.720 --> 53:20.680
<font color="yellow">Patrice, this is Inspector Mooney.</font>

53:20.680 --> 53:22.240
<font color="white">Jack. Please.</font>

53:22.240 --> 53:23.280
<font color="lime">Jack.</font>

53:23.280 --> 53:24.640
<font color="yellow">And this is Catherine.</font>

53:24.640 --> 53:27.480
<font color="lime">I know Patrice.</font>
<font color="lime">I am friends with his mother.</font>

53:27.480 --> 53:31.120
<font color="lime">She never mentioned you two were...</font>

53:31.120 --> 53:34.160
<font color="cyan">Sorry, Catherine, we were keeping</font>
<font color="cyan">it a secret, you know?</font>

53:34.160 --> 53:36.640
<font color="lime">I'm delighted for you both.</font>

53:38.640 --> 53:41.800
<font color="yellow">And, er, JP I think you know.</font>

53:43.920 --> 53:46.200
<font color="lime">JP. </font><font color="yellow">Patrice.</font>

53:46.200 --> 53:49.800
<font color="white">Well, Patrice, if you don't mind me</font>
<font color="white">saying, it's about time we met you.</font>

53:49.800 --> 53:51.800
<font color="white">The suspense has been killing me.</font>

53:53.320 --> 53:54.640
<font color="white">And I've prepared a speech.</font>

53:54.640 --> 53:55.760
<font color="yellow">No.</font>

53:55.760 --> 53:57.080
<font color="yellow">Please.</font>

53:57.080 --> 53:59.920
<font color="white">Ah, don't worry, you'll be</font>
<font color="white">too busy to hear it now, anyway.</font>

53:59.920 --> 54:02.840
<font color="cyan">I will? </font><font color="white">Well, you'll be</font>
<font color="white">getting the drinks in.</font>

54:02.840 --> 54:04.040
<font color="cyan">Oh-ho, yes.</font>

54:04.040 --> 54:05.680
<font color="cyan">On their way.</font>

54:07.240 --> 54:08.920
<font color="lime">He's such a nice boy.</font>

54:08.920 --> 54:10.120
<font color="yellow">He really is.</font>

54:10.120 --> 54:12.800
<font color="white">Much better than the last one,</font>
<font color="white">eh, JP?</font>

54:14.600 --> 54:15.840
<font color="cyan">Inspector.</font>

54:15.840 --> 54:17.440
<font color="lime">Good evening, Commissioner.</font>

54:17.440 --> 54:18.880
<font color="lime">Will you join us?</font>

54:18.880 --> 54:21.600
<font color="cyan">Good evening. No,</font>
<font color="cyan">I simply came to congratulate you</font>

54:21.600 --> 54:23.160
<font color="cyan">on your recent success.</font>

54:23.160 --> 54:24.360
<font color="cyan">A job well done.</font>

54:24.360 --> 54:26.280
<font color="white">It was a team effort, sir.</font>

54:26.280 --> 54:28.400
<font color="cyan">I'm sure it was.</font>
<font color="cyan">And speaking of the team,</font>

54:28.400 --> 54:31.240
<font color="cyan">your new officer,</font>
<font color="cyan">she will be joining you shortly.</font>

54:31.240 --> 54:32.880
<font color="white">Excellent. </font><font color="lime">It's a she?</font>

54:32.880 --> 54:35.040
<font color="cyan">Yes, Officer Ruby Patterson.</font>

54:35.040 --> 54:37.080
<font color="white">Excellent.</font>

54:37.080 --> 54:38.960
<font color="white">We look forward to it, sir.</font>

54:38.960 --> 54:40.200
<font color="cyan">Good.</font>

54:43.240 --> 54:45.120
<font color="yellow">Patterson?</font>

54:45.120 --> 54:48.120
<font color="white">Patterson - not a relation,</font>
<font color="white">is it, sir?</font>

54:48.120 --> 54:49.360
<font color="cyan">Yes,</font>

54:49.360 --> 54:50.760
<font color="cyan">she's my niece.</font>

54:53.400 --> 54:55.640
<font color="white">Catherine, tell Patrice</font>
<font color="white">I may need another beer.</font>

54:55.640 --> 54:58.080
<font color="lime">I know the Commissioner's niece.</font>

54:59.720 --> 55:01.120
<font color="lime">I'll get you three.</font>

55:02.960 --> 55:04.480
<font color="lime">And a bottle of rum.</font>

55:25.080 --> 55:26.920
<font color="cyan">Thanks for visiting Saint Marie Zoo.</font>

55:26.920 --> 55:28.160
<font color="cyan">Come again soon.</font>

55:28.160 --> 55:29.360
<font color="cyan">What happened to Zander?</font>

55:30.440 --> 55:32.160
<font color="lime">Zander? It's too late.</font>

55:32.160 --> 55:33.720
<font color="lime">He's dead.</font>

55:33.720 --> 55:37.280
<font color="cyan">Detective Inspector Mooney,</font>
<font color="cyan">meet Officer Ruby Patterson.</font>

55:37.280 --> 55:38.760
<font color="white">Delighted to have you here, Ruby.</font>

55:38.760 --> 55:40.760
<font color="cyan">I'm really looking forward</font>
<font color="cyan">to working with you.</font>

55:40.760 --> 55:43.360
<font color="lime">Same. Same.</font>
<font color="lime">I feel like I know you all already.</font>

55:43.360 --> 55:47.000
<font color="cyan">I know she's trying her best, sir,</font>
<font color="cyan">but she's just so extra.</font>

55:47.000 --> 55:49.640
<font color="lime">You are way better than my uncle</font>
<font color="lime">described you.</font>

55:49.640 --> 55:52.080
<font color="lime">Hold him down...</font>
<font color="lime">while I get my cuffs.</font>

55:52.080 --> 55:54.120
<font color="white">SHOT FIRED</font>
<font color="cyan">Ah!</font>

55:54.120 --> 55:55.160
<font color="cyan">You shot me.</font>

